5. COMMUNICATION PROTOCOLS & DATA FLOW

5.1 Internal Communication Matrix

Source → Destination Protocol Purpose Security
Michael → Gabriel gRPC/Protobuf Security alerts Mutual TLS
Gabriel → Raphael Async Events Performance feedback Message signing
Raphael → Michael Direct API Health status Certificate-based
All → Eagle Eye Telemetry Stream System state End-to-end encryption
Eagle Eye → All Command Channel Strategic directives Quantum-resistant crypto

5.2 Data Flow Architecture

```
Raw Data → [Earth: Storage] → [Water: Processing] 
           ↓
[Fire: Analysis] → [Air: Insight Generation]
           ↓
[Triad Coordination] → [Eagle Eye Synthesis]
           ↓
[Quintessence Emergence] → Action/Decision
```

5.3 API Design Principles

1. Elemental Consistency: Each API endpoint corresponds to an elemental function
2. Idempotent Operations: All modifications are safely repeatable
3. Progressive Enhancement: Capability discovery through feature flags
4. Backward Compatibility: Versioned APIs with migration paths

