6. SECURITY & RESILIENCE MECHANISMS

6.1 Multi-Layer Security Architecture

Layer 1: Infrastructure Security (Earth)

· Hardware security modules (HSMs)
· Immutable audit logs using blockchain
· Geographic distribution for disaster recovery

Layer 2: Network Security (Water)

· Zero-trust architecture
· Microsegmentation with service mesh
· DDoS protection with adaptive rate limiting

Layer 3: Compute Security (Fire)

· Secure enclaves (Intel SGX/AMD SEV)
· Homomorphic encryption for sensitive computations
· Adversarial training for ML models

Layer 4: Strategic Security (Air)

· Threat intelligence sharing
· Predictive attack modeling
· Deception technologies (honeypots)

6.2 Resilience Patterns

1. Graceful Degradation: System maintains core functions during partial failures
2. Circuit Breakers: Prevent cascading failures through intelligent isolation
3. Chaos Engineering: Regular failure injection to test resilience
4. Self-Healing: Automated recovery from predefined failure modes

6.3 Quantum Resistance

· Post-quantum cryptography for all external communications
· Quantum key distribution for internal secure channels
· Quantum-resistant digital signatures for audit trails

